config MESHTASTIC_PKI
	bool "PKC for direct messages (Curve25519/X25519 + AES-CCM)"
	depends on MESHTASTIC_NODEDB && MESHTASTIC_SETTINGS
	help
	  Implements Meshtastic public-key cryptography for direct messages,
	  interoperable with the reference firmware: an X25519 keypair (generated
	  once, persisted in the SecurityConfig NVS partition — survives reboot and
	  reflash), advertised via User.public_key, with AES-256-CCM DM
	  encrypt/decrypt (key = SHA256(ECDH shared secret)). Fixes both the
	  "PKI send failed, no public key" a peer sees and the NO_CHANNEL a peer
	  returns for our PSK-only DMs.

	  Requires PSA crypto: ECDH + ECC Montgomery-255 (key pair
	  generate/import/export + public key), AES, CCM and SHA-256. On the net
	  build the ECC/AES/SHA pieces come from the TLS overlay; the overlay adds
	  PSA_WANT_ALG_CCM.
